jerusalem -lrb- ap -rrb- _ saying `` our rifle is ready , '' palestinian leader yasser arafat hinted darkly at armed conflict sunday , prompting a sharp rebuke from israel . the escalation of rhetoric came as u.s. envoy dennis ross sought to jump start implementation of the latest mideast peace accord . a senior adviser to israeli prime minister benjamin netanyahu said arafat 's comments were a `` declaration of war on the peace process . '' david bar-illan told the associated press that netanyahu `` views such statements with the utmost severity , '' and would bring them up when his cabinet meets this week before israel begins withdrawing troops from the west bank . an israeli official , speaking on condition of anonymity , said the government had asked the united states , which mediated the recent peace agreement , to condemn arafat 's comments . 